{
  "stem": "107.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they got furious and made mistakes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Oh, we start from the beginning, and it was endless.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Outside in front of-- in-- in the mud, and depending what weather there was.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It fall, you know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It then was very soon, winter.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the winter up there is very-- very heavy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's flat, and it's not a hill.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Very far in the back you see some high mountains, which I think belonged already to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was a border there, but the area there is flat.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When it's windy, you know there's it's no protection.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It just blows you away.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I was young, and I had a decent work.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Most people had nothing to do.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, a few people who were useful to the camp were used-- an electrician, or a plumber, or-- not that there was plumbing, but there was a wash room where some water was.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there were latrines that had to be-- so if you were a plumber, you at least got work there and got a little more bread.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Still the clothes we came in, which was also an exception.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Later on, they'll change that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, and I was inside.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, most people had to go out of their barracks to go to the latrines, the toilets, which was sometimes a walk of half an hour in the mud for all the people.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At the beginning, and then, of course, the shoes got stuck in the mud, and they had only one shoe.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had shoes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, I was still in the hospital.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had some advantages.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "First of all, when patients died, there remained a little bit bread or an extra soup, which was distributed to the personnel, or sometimes we give it to the patients, too, but we slowly got a little bit more adjusted to life in a camp and thought about ourselves.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I had still the advantage of being a doctor there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a barrack, and they said, you make a hospital.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we made the hospital.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was one sergeant-- master sergeant, we would call it in military, an SS man, an elderly man who was a medic, which was a kind of nurse, over nurse, who did take care of all the things as a big shot doctor, SS doctor, but not one to get involved with.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was the middle man between what we badly need, and he was very decent.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm really sad that I don't know, but I knew that they had somehow saved his life.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Some of our survivors saved his life after that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Otherwise, he would have been working with Mengele and his doctors.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He would've been executed, and he was the person to approach and tell him-- we said, we need badly insulin.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he would tell her, insulin is not allowed to give to Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What the logic is, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Serum-- we had a terrible diphtheria epidemic.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Serum, which is made out of the blood of people who had the illness is not allowed to give to Jews.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So people died until we found some way to deal with the others.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was even medically a very interesting situation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We had no x-rays.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We had to listen to the chest to find when people had pneumonia, and they did have pneumonia.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It didn't help us too much, because antibiotics were not invented yet, but chemotherapy, which outside was available was not available for us, except a black market smuggled in for people who ported in with the transportation, which they are transports.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were somewhere else, and the luggage remained.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Diphtheria, pneumonia, menigitis-- severe ones.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then there were very bad [INAUDIBLE] infections of the legs, because the people lost their shoes, they had cuts on their feet.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The cuts got infected, and some-- there  you saw things that you usually don't see.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When we approached the sergeant, we said, we cannot treat this.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We have no means to treat this well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He said, you should see our soldier on the Russian front.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they had found some kind of justification.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Say to-- say I have to suffer on the-- so at the Russian front.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Or--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not in our-- we were a privileged camp for six months.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, the question was, why?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Our speculation was the same thing we had heard about Theresienstadt and the Red Cross that the Red Cross had heard about Auschwitz, and they wanted to show the Red Cross, look, the whole families live here, can get together.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was the only explanation we could assume.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I have never found out what the reason was.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "After six months, everybody-- everybody was supposed to be transported another camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Detours came.",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
